.TH HIGH 1 "March 2026" "high 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
high \- Terminal-based LLM chat interface with low-latency streaming
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B high
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIPROMPT\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B high
is a minimalist, terminal-based interface for Large Language Models (LLMs)
designed for low-latency feedback. It features zero-latency streaming with
preview mode, smart syntax highlighting, conversation management, and
seamless Unix pipeline integration.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-api " " \fIURL\fR
API base endpoint (default: http://localhost:8042/v1)
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-model " " \fIMODEL\fR
Model to use for chat completion
.TP
.BR \-M ", " \-\-ask\-model
Interactive model selection
.TP
.BR \-L ", " \-\-models
List available models
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-continue " " \fITITLE\fR
Continue from saved conversation (appends to same file)
.TP
.BR \-C ", " \-\-continue\-last
Continue from last conversation (appends to same file)
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-isolate
Branch conversation (save as new conversation instead of appending)
.RS
When used with \fB\-c\fR or \fB\-C\fR, creates a new conversation branched from
the specified one instead of appending to the existing file.
.RE
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list
List saved conversations (interactive TUI with fzf-style navigation)
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-show " " \fITITLE\fR
Show a saved conversation
.TP
.BR \-S ", " \-\-show\-last
Show last saved conversation
.TP
.BR \-x ", " \-\-http\-proxy " " \fIURL\fR
HTTP proxy URL
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-format
Enable markdown formatting
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-raw
Output raw JSON (for debugging)
.TP
.BR \-F ", " \-\-no\-format
Plain text output (no markdown, overrides \fB\-f\fR and env vars)
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-preview
Preview code blocks with ghost text (zero-latency streaming)
.TP
.B \-\-md
Enable markdown syntax highlighting
.TP
.BR \-\-tps " " \fIRATE\fR
Tokens per second for streaming (controls output speed)
.TP
.BR \-\-chunk\-size " " \fIN\fR
Characters per token chunk (default: 1)
.TP
.BR \-R ", " \-\-role " " \fIROLE\fR
System role/prompt
.TP
.BR \-\-theme " " \fITHEME\fR
Syntax highlight theme (default: xoria256)
.TP
.BR \-\-max\-tokens " " \fIN\fR
Maximum response tokens
.TP
.BR \-\-log\-file " " \fIPATH\fR
Log to file
.TP
.BR \-\-tab\-width " " \fIN\fR
Tab width in spaces (default: 8, env: LLM_TAB_WIDTH)
.TP
.B \-\-config\-dump
Output config as environment variables (for ~/.bashrc)
.TP
.B \-\-remove\-think\-tags
Strip <think> ... </think> tags from assistant output (DeepSeek-R1 style)
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Show version information
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message
.SH CONVERSATION MODES
.TP
.B \-c TITLE
Continue from saved conversation TITLE, append to same file
.TP
.B \-C
Continue from last conversation, append to same file
.TP
.B \-c TITLE \-i
Branch from TITLE, save as NEW conversation
.TP
.B \-C \-i
Branch from last conversation, save as NEW conversation
.TP
.B (none)
Start fresh conversation with auto-generated title
.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
.B LLM_API_BASE
API endpoint URL (default: http://localhost:8042/v1)
.TP
.B LLM_CONFIG_DIR
Configuration directory (default: ~/.config/high)
.TP
.B LLM_SYSTEM_ROLE
Default system prompt (default: "You are a helpful assistant.")
.TP
.B LLM_MAX_TOKENS
Maximum tokens for response (default: 0 = unlimited)
.TP
.B LLM_TEMPERATURE
Sampling temperature 0.0-2.0 (default: 1.0)
.TP
.B LLM_TIMEOUT
Request timeout in seconds (default: 36000)
.TP
.B LLM_FORMAT_MARKDOWN
Enable markdown formatting 1/0 (default: 1)
.TP
.B LLM_VERBOSE
Verbose output 1/0 (default: 0)
.TP
.B LLM_RAW_OUTPUT
Raw JSON output 1/0 (default: 0)
.TP
.B LLM_TAB_WIDTH
Tab expansion width 1-16 (default: 8)
.TP
.B HIGHLIGHT_THEME
Syntax highlighting theme (default: xoria256)
.TP
.B HIGH_PREVIEW_CODE
Enable code preview mode 1/0 (default: 0)
.TP
.B HIGH_MARKDOWN_SYNTAX
Enable markdown highlighting 1/0 (default: 1)
.TP
.B HTTP_PROXY
HTTP proxy URL
.SH EXTRA UTILITIES
After running \fBsudo make install-extras\fR, two additional utilities are available:
.SS pre \- File Context Provider
Injects file contents with proper markdown codeblocks into LLM prompts.
.TP
.B Features
Automatic language detection, recursive directory scanning (maxdepth 2),
proper trailing newline handling, full path resolution.
.TP
.B Usage
.B pre src/main.cpp | high -m Qwen3.5 -f -p --md "Review this code"
.br
.B pre src/*.*pp | high -m Kimi-K2.5 -f -p --md "Analyze the architecture"
.br
.B pre ./src "*.py" | high -f -p --md "Find all Python files"
.TP
.B Supported Extensions
sh, bash, zsh, py, js, ts, rb, go, rs, c, cc, cpp, h, hpp, java, cs, php,
html, htm, css, json, xml, yaml, yml, md, sql
.SS cb \- Interactive Codeblock Extractor
Extracts codeblocks from high output (or any markdown source) with interactive selection.
.TP
.B Features
Parses markdown codeblocks, interactive TUI with fzf, preview with syntax
highlighting (requires bat/batcat), automatic clipboard copy (requires xclip).
.TP
.B Usage
.B high -s myconv -F | cb
.br
.B pre "*.md" | cb
.TP
.B Dependencies
Required: fzf, awk. Optional: bat/batcat (enhanced preview), xclip (clipboard).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Basic usage:
.B high "What is the capital of France?"
.TP
With specific model:
.B high -m llama-3 "Explain quantum computing"
.TP
Continue last conversation:
.B high -C "Add more details about..."
.TP
Branch from last conversation (create new):
.B high -C -i "Try a different approach"
.TP
List conversations:
.B high -l
.TP
Show conversation without think tags:
.B high -s myconv --remove-think-tags
.TP
Pipe from curl:
.B curl -s https://example.com/api | high "Summarize this"
.TP
Export configuration:
.B high --config-dump >> ~/.bashrc
.TP
Use with pre utility:
.B pre src/*.cpp | high "Review this code for security issues"
.TP
Extract codeblocks from conversation:
.B high -S -F | cb
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/high/conversations/
Directory containing saved conversations (JSON format)
.TP
.I /usr/local/share/high/
Extra utilities (pre, cb) after \fBmake install-extras\fR
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/pre
Alias script for pre utility
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/cb
Alias script for cb utility
